"a.唠叨的，多话的 【英】 adj. 唠叨的，多话的(loqu acious; talkative)；喋喋不 休的(talking too much) 【记】 来自词根:garr(唠叨) 【考】 garrulous : talkative / cloying : sweet(喋喋不休是过分多话 /腻是过分甜)反义词：laconic(简 洁的) 【记】 garr(闲聊)+ulous→ 唠叨的 【例】 It is very difficult to interrupt a garrulous person. adj. (有关琐屑或漫无目的的话题, 让人厌恶地)唠叨的, 多话的 = loquacious = talkative 【记】garr聊, ulous多－唠叨的gar嘎嘎叫, rul = rule(n 规则), ous多: 鸭子规则－唠叨的 【类】garrulous: talkative = cloying: sweet = fussy: careful唠叨是让人厌恶的多话 = 腻是让人厌恶的甜 = 爱挑剔的是让人厌恶的仔细garrulous[loquacious]: words = prodigal: money多话的浪费话语 = 浪费的浪费钱 【反】laconic(adj 说话简洁的) 【记】garr- 聊天；gar- 象声，+ ruler 支配，统治，嘎嘎嘎地来支配别人，真是喋喋不休 garrulous (adj.)  1610s, from Latin garrulus ""talkative,"" from garrire ""to chatter,"" from PIE root *gar- ""to call, cry,"" of imitative origin (compare Greek gerys ""voice, sound,"" Ossetic zar ""song,"" Welsh garm, Old Irish gairm ""noise, cry""). Related: Garrulously; garrulousness."
